Today is my 34th birthday! I’m extremely thankful for everything God has blessed me with from the good to the bad. Most of all I’m extremely thankful for my son. MJ changed me for the best. He gave my life purpose and pushed me to do things I was once afraid of. In being a mom I learned to be patient and calm.  I’ve learned to practice what I preach. I’ve learned to never give up and nothing is impossible. While teaching my son to be confident and to believe in himself, it reminded I had to do the same. I’m on a new journey in my life and I must say it’s scary but I’m enjoying the ride. MJ thank you for changing my life……. Happy Birthday to me… ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

18 months ago, I took the leap to return to school, aspiring to become a Registered Nurse. Honestly, I was unsure of how I’d navigate it, but there was this determination to see it through this time. I turned to prayer, seeking guidance, strength, and the discipline needed for this journey. Going back to school brought out sacrifices I didn’t know I had in me, like saying  farewell to shopping – a tough one! 😩😔 Balancing a strict budget, limited outings, and working 2 to 3 days a week, all while juggling the roles of a full-time mom and student, and paying for school out of pocket. They weren’t kidding when they said it takes a village. The love and support I received, especially from those closest to me, made all the difference. It wasn’t an easy journey, but I made it through. 🎓✨I DID IT 😊
Thank you so much for all the love ❤️
